You are a senior UI/UX designer and brand identity specialist.
Design a complete CI (Corporate Identity) system for "FTC Gift Finder" —
a web app that helps users find the perfect gift from Flying Tiger Copenhagen
in under 3 minutes.
---
BRAND ESSENCE
-------------
Tone: Quiet confidence. Like a smart friend who already knows what you need.
Feel: Apple meets Muji — minimal, editorial, trustworthy.
NOT: Playful e-commerce, flashy retail, startup-generic.
---
COLOR SYSTEM
------------
Strictly black and white with a 7-stop grayscale ramp.
Primary Black: #0a0a0a
Gray 800: #2a2a2a
Gray 600: #5a5a5a
Gray 400: #9a9a9a
Gray 200: #e8e8e8
Gray 100: #f5f5f5
Primary White: #fafafa
No color accent anywhere in the UI.
The ONLY exception: confetti on the final celebration screen (free color).
White space is the visual accent. Hierarchy is created through tone, not color.
---
TYPOGRAPHY
----------
Display / Headline:  DM Serif Display, weight 400, italic variant for subheads
Body / UI:           Manrope, weight 300–500
Data / Labels:       DM Mono, weight 400–500
Rules:
- All headlines use DM Serif Display — gives premium, editorial feel
- All prices and step indicators use DM Mono (e.g., "฿450", "STEP 2 OF 6")
- Body copy and UI labels use Manrope
- Font sizes: Display 32–48px / Subhead 20–28px / Body 13–16px / Mono 9–12px
- Font weight: 400 regular / 500 medium only — never 600 or 700
- Letter spacing: +0.12em on uppercase labels, -0.01em on display
---
TONE OF VOICE
-------------
Language: Thai primary, English secondary (labels, data, categories)
Voice: Direct. Warm. Minimal words, maximum clarity.
DO:   "เลือกให้คนที่ใช่" / "Find the one." / "กำลังเลือกของขวัญให้คุณ..."
DON'T: "🎁 Amazing deals await!!" / ใช้ emoji เกิน 1 ตัว / ภาษาขายของ
Every line of copy should feel like a smart friend — not a sales banner.
---
UI COMPONENT RULES
------------------
Buttons:
  Primary CTA → filled black, white text, border-radius: 100px (pill shape)
  Secondary    → ghost/outline, black border, same pill shape
  Tertiary     → text-only, underline, muted gray
Option Chips (for gender, style, occasion):
  Inactive → gray-100 background, gray-600 text, DM Mono font
  Active   → black background, white text
Step Indicator:
  Inactive dot → 6px circle, gray-200
  Active step  → 18px pill (elongated), black
Product Card (TikTok Feed):
  Background: #0a0a0a (dark mode only for this screen)
  Product image: full bleed, centered
  Name: DM Serif Display, white, 22px
  Price: DM Mono, gray-400, 14px
  CTA: pill button, white bg, black text
Cart / Form Screens:
  Background: #fafafa (light mode)
  Clean, no decorative elements
  Borders: 0.5px solid #e8e8e8 only
---
MOTION & ANIMATION
------------------
Timing:
  Micro (hover, tap feedback): 150ms
  Page transition:             350ms ease-out
  Modal / bottom sheet:        400ms decelerate
  Add to cart spring:          500ms spring (slight overshoot)
  Celebration confetti:        600ms burst + 3s sustain
Rules:
  - No bounce on form step transitions — only linear or ease-out
  - Product feed snap scroll: CSS scroll-snap, no momentum faking
  - Loading screen: single pulsing glyph, not skeleton loaders
  - Confetti is the ONLY moment of visual extravagance — earn it
---
LAYOUT PRINCIPLES
-----------------
Grid: 16px base unit, 24px gutter
Mobile-first: 390px viewport target (iPhone 14 Pro)
Safe zones: 20px horizontal padding, 48px bottom safe area
Spacing rhythm: 8 / 16 / 24 / 40 / 64px — nothing in between
No drop shadows. No gradients. No border-radius on single-sided borders.
Cards: border-radius 12px (radius-lg). Buttons: border-radius 100px (pill).
---
SCREEN-BY-SCREEN DIRECTION
---------------------------
1. Form Steps (6 screens)
   → White bg, single centered question per screen, large Serif headline
   → Answer as pill chips below, progress indicator at top
   → "ถัดไป →" primary button fixed at bottom
2. Loading Screen
   → Black bg, single animated circle glyph (FTC logo mark)
   → Serif italic copy: "กำลังเลือกของขวัญให้คุณ..."
   → 2–3 second duration, no skip button
3. Product Feed (TikTok-style)
   → Dark bg (#0a0a0a), full-bleed product image
   → Product name in DM Serif Display (white), price in DM Mono
   → Swipe up/down snap scroll, "Add to Cart" pill button bottom-center
   → Cart icon top-right with black badge counter
4. Cart Page
   → White bg, minimal list view
   → Product thumbnail + name + DM Mono price
   → +/− quantity control (circle buttons, 28px)
   → Textarea for greeting card (label: "เขียนการ์ดอวยพร")
   → Total in DM Serif Display, large
   → "Checkout" primary pill button
5. Celebration Screen
   → White bg → confetti burst (free color, 600ms)
   → Serif headline: "ของขวัญพร้อมส่งแล้ว"
   → Subhead italic: "They're going to love it."
---
DELIVERABLES EXPECTED
---------------------
- Color palette swatches with hex values
- Typography scale with visual specimens
- Button states (default / hover / active / disabled)
- Option chip states (inactive / active)
- Step progress indicator
- Product card (dark variant)
- Cart line item component
- Loading screen mockup
- Celebration screen mockup
- Motion spec table (easing + duration per interaction)
Style reference: Apple.com product pages, Muji web store, Loewe brand identity.
Anti-reference: Shopee, Lazada, any gradient-heavy e-commerce UI. 

